The paper deals with the computation of consequences of a logic program, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The use of unfounded sets and well-founded negation is a common technique in logic programming (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the computation of dominators in a flowgraph, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the simulation of well-founded justification and well-founded domination for certain classes of logic programs, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
